comments.body: To be conservative in rolling this out for PUL records, you could make a filter to only display the 583 if there is a $8 in the field to identify it as coming from a holding. There was some concern before about showing 583 fields in records. Currently, the 583 is only shown if it is a PULFA record. But for partner records from SCSB, we will not have such ability to filter.
Sample record in the sandbox is 99126831126106421.

I updated the publishing profile DACS Test Record Export in the sandbox to include the 583s from holdings and the item retention info.

The Committed to Retain flag will be in 876$w.
The Retention Reason will be in 876$x.

comments.body:
I'm struggling to get the "verify" test passing (copy-pasted from the Special Collections role) 

```
  PLAY [Verify] ******************************************************************
  
  TASK [test for presence byzantine sudoer commands] *****************************
  ok: [instance] => (item=deploy ALL=(ALL) NOPASSWD: /usr/sbin/service apache2 *)
  ok: [instance] => (item=Runas_Alias WWW = www-data)
  ok: [instance] => (item=deploy ALL = (WWW) NOPASSWD: ALL)
  failed: [instance] (item=deploy ALL=(ALL) NOPASSWD: /bin/chown -R www-data /var/www/byzantine*) => {"ansible_loop_var": "item", "backup": "", "changed": true, "failed_when_result": true, "item": "deploy ALL=(ALL) NOPASSWD: /bin/chown -R www-data /var/www/byzantine*", "msg": "line added"}
  failed: [instance] (item=deploy ALL=(ALL) NOPASSWD: /bin/chown -R deploy /var/www/byzantine*) => {"ansible_loop_var": "item", "backup": "", "changed": true, "failed_when_result": true, "item": "deploy ALL=(ALL) NOPASSWD: /bin/chown -R deploy /var/www/byzantine*", "msg": "line added"}
```

It looks like these are connected to the changes made in the Capistrano role - see https://github.com/pulibrary/princeton_ansible/blob/1b8729d23ea8a607ff47212961280eccfafd4669/roles/capistrano/tasks/main.yml#L55-L74
